article.headline: South Florida 74, St. Francis, NY 71
article.story: TAMPA, Fla. -- Ron Anderson Jr. scored 16 points to lead three South Florida players in double figures in a 74-71 victory over St. Francis (N.Y.) on Monday night. Shaun Noriega and Jawanza Poland added 15 points each for the Bulls (1-1). Noriega had all but one of his points in the first half, as South Florida took a 38-31 lead at halftime. His free throw with 6.1 seconds left in the game gave the Bulls a four-point lead. Ricky Cadell led St. Francis (0-2) with 28 points. Stefan Perunicic added 13 points and Akeem Bennett had 12 for the Terriers, who led 20-13 midway through the first half.
